main event: A possible satellite was observed over the Pacific Ocean on November 20, 1964.
interesting points: The object was described as being the size and brightness of a first magnitude star.
The object was observed at an altitude of 35 degrees above the horizon, moving from west to east.
The observation lasted for approximately 10 minutes, from 0950Z to 1000Z.
No photographs or physical evidence were available, and the object was not detected on radar.
The report was classified as a possible satellite sighting.
sighted object: a bright object in the sky
